cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.HC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on analyzing the behavior of users on social networking sites, which falls under the domain of social and information networks. 
2. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the impact of social networking sites on society and how users shift their behavior towards new platforms, which falls under the domain of computers and society. 
3. cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) - The paper analyzes the social behavior of users on social networking sites and how it affects the success of new platforms, which falls under the domain of social and behavioral sciences. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper discusses the features of social networking sites and how they affect user behavior, which falls under the domain of human-computer interaction. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may also fall under the domain of multimedia as it discusses the features of social networking sites and how they affect user behavior in terms of multimedia content.
